Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION recognizing National Girls
2 and Women in Sports Day (NGWSD).
3 Whereas, National Girls and Women in Sports Day
4 (NGWSD) was founded in 1987 in remembrance and honor of
5 Olympic volleyball player, Flo Hyman;
6 Whereas, Flo Hyman was known for her athletic
7 achievements and dedication to promoting equality for women's
8 sports;
9 Whereas, NGWSD is co-founded and powered by the
10 Women's Sports Foundation and is supported by its team of
11 champion athletes. NGWSD annually hosts over 300 grassroots
12 events across all 50 states and Washington D.C., with an
13 estimated reach of 200,000 girls and women;
14 Whereas, NGWSD serves as a reminder of Flo's legacy but
15 has also grown to advocate for girls and women in sports all
16 over the nation, acknowledging their positive impact and
17 ongoing struggle for the equality of women's sports;
2026 DR 3837/DI ol

2
1 Whereas, Since the first National Girls and Women in
2 Sports Day in 1987, there has been a vast expansion of athletic
3 opportunities for women in Indiana;
4 Whereas, Women's basketball, volleyball, soccer, tennis,
5 wrestling, gymnastics, swimming, and diving have all seen
6 tremendous growth in participation from girls and women
7 across Indiana;
8 Whereas, Through the leadership of the Indiana Sports
9 Corp, Indiana has maintained a focus on uplifting women's
10 sports while becoming a world-class sporting event center.
11 Indiana has developed some of the best women's sports
12 programs and facilities, such as Indy Ignite, the Marvella youth
13 sports complex, and the renowned basketball team, the Indiana
14 Fever; and
15 Whereas, NGWSD inspires girls and women to engage in
16 sports, and celebrate the courage, strength, leadership, and
17 confidence derived from women's sports: Therefore,
18 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
19 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
20 SECTION 1. That the Indiana State Senate recognizes the
21 National Girls and Women in Sports Day.
22 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
23 to transmit a copy of this Resolution to Indiana Sports Corp.
